<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-281-548  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 281 548.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  May 11 1989 n1163 p19(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Are you sitting comfortably? (computer workplace safety)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barrett, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ergonomically designed workstations and offices and sensible workpatterns can do much to alleviate such computer-associatedproblems as blurred sight, backache and repetitive strain injuries(RSI).andP;  Health is a delicate area of negotiation between users andmanagement.andP;  The majority of VDT-related ailments are caused bypoor ergonomic design of the workplace.andP;  Eyestrain is caused byglare, reflection from windows, close focusing at the screen andworking without breaks.andP;  VDT radiation hazards are now thought tobe minimal, but older terminals may still pose a threat.andO;Electro-magnetic radiation from power cabling may also pose athreat.andP;  Studies indicate that VDT users work better and moreaccurately if allowed to work at their own speed and that VDT workmay degrade subsequent performance.andP;  A list of relevant books andpamphlets is provided.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ErgonomicsOccupational HealthSafetyWork EnvironmentEmployee RelationsRadiationData Entry PersonnelKeyboardsVDTsStressJob SatisfactionEconomics of Computing.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>